      "id": "commentary",
      "html": "<h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The lack of a praenomen on the stone means that it is most likely that the epitaph was for a woman, most plausibly called Claudia Fortunata, but as Bivona observes there are instances of male individuals lacking a praenomen in the Termini corpus also (e.g. <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000056\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000153</a>), so this is hardly conclusive.</p>  "
